-- BMW to Export 10,000 More 3-Series Cars to China as Demand Grows, FTD Says
-- Aaron Kirchfeld
-- 2010-07-13T05:11:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-13/bmw-to-export-10-000-more-3-series-cars-to-china-as-demand-grows-ftd-says.html

          
          
             Bayerische Motoren Werke AG  plans to
export 10,000 additional 3-Series vehicles from its Munich plant
to China this year to meet growing demand, Financial Times
Deutschland reported, citing BMW personnel chief  Harald Krueger .  
 BMW is exporting the vehicles to China, which are subject
to an import tax of 25 percent, because production capacity in
the country canâ€™t keep up with demand, the newspaper said.  
 The German carmaker also plans to seek an agreement on
longer working hours with the works council in Germany, FTD
said.  
